internet-monitor (1.0.1-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Security and code quality improvements
  * Fix command injection vulnerabilities by using safe argument arrays
  * Replace shell-based DNS testing with Ruby Resolv library
  * Rename Logger class to InternetMonitorLogger to avoid conflicts
  * Replace global variable with SignalHandler class for better encapsulation
  * Improve error handling for file operations and log rotation
  * Add comprehensive configuration validation with range checks
  * Add debug logging level for troubleshooting
  * Update Debian packaging standards version to 4.7.0
  * Add explicit Ruby version requirement (>= 2.7)
  * Enhance README with security and troubleshooting sections

 -- Jory A. Pratt, W5GLE <geekypenguin@gmail.com>  Thu, 23 Jan 2026 12:33:54 +0000

internet-monitor (1.0.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial Debian package release
  * Ruby implementation of Internet Monitor for AllStarLink ASL3+
  * Features:
    - Automatic internet connectivity monitoring
    - Audio announcements for connection status changes
    - Automatic log rotation
    - Network recovery attempts
    - Systemd service integration

 -- Jory A. Pratt, W5GLE <geekypenguin@gmail.com>  Mon, 01 Jan 2026 12:00:00 +0000
